        <section>
            <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
            <p>Cookies are small data files stored on a user's device by a website. They help websites remember information about visitors, such as login status or preferences.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How Do Cookies Work?</h2>
            <p>When you visit a website, the server sends a cookie to your browser. The browser stores it and sends it back to the server with each subsequent request, allowing the website to maintain stateful information.</p>
        </section>
